"n. 奴隸，农奴 【英】 n.奴隸，农奴(a servant slave；bondman) 【记】 注意thrall构词：ent hrall(迷住，吸引住) n. 奴隸; 农奴(受枷锁束缚的人) 【记】th死, r, all: 所有的奴隸都会死. 【参】enthrall(v 奴役; 迷住, 吸引住) 【记】throw + all 所有东西都被扔出去了，一无所有的奴隸；音：丝绕，被丝，绳子束缚的奴隸； thrall (n.)  late Old English þræl ""bondman, serf, slave,"" from a Scandinavian source akin to Old Norse þræll ""slave, servant,"" figuratively ""wretch, scoundrel,"" probably from Proto-Germanic *thrakhilaz, literally ""runner,"" from root *threh- ""to run"" (cognates: Old High German dregil ""servant,"" properly ""runner;"" Old English þrægan, Gothic þragjan ""to run""). Meaning ""condition of servitude"" is from early 14c."
